<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="33">
Gosline (1953) established the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:50FF7E9C-72DE-4852-A9B0-75171AFEB327" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula Gosline 1953:218" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microbrotula</taxonomicName>
for two species of livebearing brotulas from coral reef and rubble areas in Hawaii, with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3662C4A7-C2F3-4148-A660-D8573C286A49" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula rubra Gosline 1953:219" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubra">M. rubra</taxonomicName>
the type species. The second species, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:22B378B5-B56C-4411-885B-3F6CD37AEB25" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula nigra Gosline 1953:220" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigra">M. nigra</taxonomicName>
, was transferred to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8F20D4FB-6778-41A0-90E4-7C9C1E3E21B1" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Oligopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oligopus Risso 1810:141" order="Coleoptera" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Oligopus Risso</taxonomicName>
where it was a homonym and renamed 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F38CB96E-3022-4D75-A0B0-3E2FAFC55FBB" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Oligopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oligopus waikiki Cohen 1964:11" order="Coleoptera" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waikiki">O. waikiki</taxonomicName>
, now 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Grammonus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="waikiki">Grammonus waikiki</taxonomicName>
(Cohen, 1964; Nielsen and Cohen, 1999). Within their redefined subfamily Bythitinae, family Bythitidae, Cohen and Nielsen (1978) suggested 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:50FF7E9C-72DE-4852-A9B0-75171AFEB327" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula Gosline 1953:218" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microbrotula</taxonomicName>
might be a shallow-water derivative of the bathyal genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:27734AC6-B1F1-4B63-9AEA-1458C839AD13" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Cataetyx" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cataetyx GÃ¼nther 1887:104" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cataetyx</taxonomicName>
. Machida (2000) considered his new genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:385B5B0F-4AD2-4F5A-9F57-DACAFFA2D0F2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Acarobythites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Acarobythites Machida 2000:123" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Acarobythites</taxonomicName>
close to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:50FF7E9C-72DE-4852-A9B0-75171AFEB327" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula Gosline 1953:218" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microbrotula</taxonomicName>
which it resembles in many characters, but differs from it in its lack of scales, 11-12 caudal-fin rays, morphology of the anteriormost neural spines, vomerine teeth arranged in a single row, indistinct lateral line and short pectoral and pelvic fins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageNumber="34" pageNumber="33">
Cohen and Wourms (1976) described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:987849EC-C385-4058-BB54-E7B9CD3E32FB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula randalli Cohen &amp; Wourms 1976:82" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="randalli">Microbrotula randalli</taxonomicName>
from five specimens taken on reefs at Efate Island, Vanuatu, and American Samoa. Additional material I have examined is listed below. Cohen and Nielsen (1978) alluded to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:50FF7E9C-72DE-4852-A9B0-75171AFEB327" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula Gosline 1953:218" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microbrotula</taxonomicName>
specimens from the Red Sea, and Nielsen and Cohen (1999) stated that several undescribed species occur in the Indo-Pacific region. The first southwestern Indian Ocean record of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:50FF7E9C-72DE-4852-A9B0-75171AFEB327" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula Gosline 1953:218" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microbrotula</taxonomicName>
was brought to my attention from scuba collections made by Mr. Andy Bentley at Aliwal Shoal, South Africa, in the summer of 2002. The purpose of this paper is to describe this material and re-diagnose 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:50FF7E9C-72DE-4852-A9B0-75171AFEB327" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula Gosline 1953:218" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microbrotula Gosline</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
